<%- include('partials/header') %>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/chrono-vendetta.css">

<nav class="navbar">
        <div class="nav-container">
            <a href="#" class="nav-logo">CHRONO VENDETTA</a>
            <ul class="nav-links">
                <li><a href="#story">Story</a></li>
                <li><a href="#characters">Characters</a></li>
                <li><a href="#chapters">Chapters</a></li>
                <li><a href="#quotes">Quotes</a></li>
                <li><a href="#journey">Journey</a></li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </nav>

    <header class="hero">
        <div class="hero-grid">
            <div class="hero-content">
                <h1 class="hero-title">Chrono Vendetta</h1>
                <div class="hero-author">Deva Harsha V</div>
                <p class="hero-tagline">Your worst enemy... might be your future.</p>
                <p class="hero-hook">
                    Aarav has spent a lifetime running from a dark truth: everywhere he goes, death follows. When the parents of his lover Meera become the latest casualties, he uncovers a terrifying shadow stalking him through time.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="book-cover-container">
                <div class="book-cover">
                    <!-- Official Book Poster Link Applied -->
                    <img src="https://cdn-gcs.inkitt.com/vertical_storycovers/d96db41aa92bbe9f6de5e31de3330675.jpg" alt="Chrono Vendetta Book Cover" class="cover-image">
                    <!-- Subtle cinematic overlay sheen -->
                    <div class="cover-overlay"></div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <a href="#story" class="scroll-indicator">
            <span>Explore Loop</span>
            <div class="scroll-mouse">
                <div class="scroll-wheel"></div>
            </div>
        </a>
    </header>

    <section id="story" class="container">
        <span class="section-label">Dossier</span>
        <h2 class="section-heading">The Synopsis</h2>
        <div class="story-layout">
            <div class="story-main">
                <div class="highlight-quote">
                    "He didn't carry a curse. He was the curse."
                </div>
                <div class="story-text">
                    <p>
                        Aarav is trapped in a vortex of guilt and isolation, haunted by thirteen mysterious deaths that have claimed every foster family and guardian who ever took him in. When his girlfriend Meera's parents die under the exact same unexplainable parameters—frozen solid in time, displaying vacant stares with no toxins or signs of force—the fragile reality he tried to build collapses completely. 
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Investigating the crime scene, Aarav uncovers a security recording that shows a figure moving inside a brief, deliberate three-second electrical freeze. The posture, the shoulder tilt, the unmistakable mechanical stance—it is his own. Confronting this mysterious stalker reveals an impossible nightmare: his future self has broken through time, utilizing an enigmatic terminal known as the Chrono Seal to aggressively murder anyone poised to betray Aarav in years to come.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="theme-container">
                    <h3 class="theme-title">Core Temporal Motifs</h3>
                    <div class="theme-tags">
                        <span class="theme-tag">Temporal Paradox</span>
                        <span class="theme-tag">Predestination</span>
                        <span class="theme-tag">Self-Fulfilling Prophecy</span>
                        <span class="theme-tag">The Burden of Paranoia</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="story-stats">
                <div class="stat-card">
                    <div class="stat-num">9</div>
                    <div class="stat-label">Chronicle Chapters</div>
                </div>
                <div class="stat-card">
                    <div class="stat-num">1</div>
                    <div class="stat-label">Primary Subject Narrator</div>
                </div>
                <div class="stat-card">
                    <div class="stat-num">5</div>
                    <div class="stat-label">Known Resets Attempted</div>
                </div>
                <div class="stat-card">
                    <div class="stat-num">Sci-Fi Thriller</div>
                    <div class="stat-label">Genre Classification</div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="characters" class="container">
        <span class="section-label">Identities</span>
        <h2 class="section-heading">Divergent Elements</h2>
        <div class="character-grid">
            <div class="character-card">
                <div class="character-header">
                    <h3 class="character-name">Aarav</h3>
                    <span class="character-role">Subject 43AAR</span>
                </div>
                <div class="character-body">
                    <p class="character-desc">A young man deeply traumatized by a lifetime of tragic losses, living a life of absolute isolation until awakening his hidden temporal anomalies.</p>
                    <div class="trait-container">
                        <span class="trait-badge">Obsessive</span>
                        <span class="trait-badge">Haunted</span>
                        <span class="trait-badge">Adaptive</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="character-card">
                <div class="character-header">
                    <h3 class="character-name">Future Aarav</h3>
                    <span class="character-role">The Temporal Vigilante</span>
                </div>
                <div class="character-body">
                    <p class="character-desc">An older, deeply scarred, and ruthless iteration of Aarav who has lived through devastating betrayals and traveled back ten years to aggressively break the loop.</p>
                    <div class="trait-container">
                        <span class="trait-badge">Merciless</span>
                        <span class="trait-badge">Controlled</span>
                        <span class="trait-badge">Exhausted</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="character-card">
                <div class="character-header">
                    <h3 class="character-name">Meera Sharma</h3>
                    <span class="character-role">The Anchor</span>
                </div>
                <div class="character-body">
                    <p class="character-desc">Aarav's romantic interest whose tragic family loss pulls her into the center of a temporal corporate tracking program labeled Project Timelock.</p>
                    <div class="trait-container">
                        <span class="trait-badge">Grieving</span>
                        <span class="trait-badge">Resolute</span>
                        <span class="trait-badge">Distanced</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="chapters" class="container">
        <span class="section-label">Structure</span>
        <h2 class="section-heading">Timeline Segments</h2>
        <div class="chapter-grid">
            <div class="chapter-card">
                <span class="chapter-num">Chapter 1</span>
                <h3 class="chapter-title">The Boy Who Brought Death</h3>
                <p class="chapter-teaser">Aarav counts the names in his battered notebook following the unexplainable deaths of Meera's parents.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="chapter-card">
                <span class="chapter-num">Chapter 2</span>
                <h3 class="chapter-title">Death Returns Home</h3>
                <p class="chapter-teaser">Returning to the empty Sharma residence, Aarav secures a hidden CCTV hard drive containing impossible truths.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="chapter-card">
                <span class="chapter-num">Chapter 3</span>
                <h3 class="chapter-title">Patterns in the Silence</h3>
                <p class="chapter-teaser">A trail leads Aarav to an old social worker, revealing that other foster children reported the identical mirror stalker.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="chapter-card">
                <span class="chapter-num">Chapter 4</span>
                <h3 class="chapter-title">Trap of the Past</h3>
                <p class="chapter-teaser">Using a hired actor as bait, Aarav setups an evening sting and comes face-to-face with an older version of himself.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="chapter-card">
                <span class="chapter-num">Chapter 5</span>
                <h3 class="chapter-title">The Face Behind the Mask</h3>
                <p class="chapter-teaser">Future Aarav displays a charred photograph, mapping out historical financial betrayals and the pulsing Chrono Seal.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="chapter-card">
                <span class="chapter-num">Chapter 6</span>
                <h3 class="chapter-title">The Second Life</h3>
                <p class="chapter-teaser">Aarav uncovers his childhood journals, realizing he has spent his entire existence dreaming of his older self watching him sleep.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="chapter-card">
                <span class="chapter-num">Chapter 7</span>
                <h3 class="chapter-title">Truth or Madness</h3>
                <p class="chapter-teaser">Meera delivers an unlabelled USB stick uncovering terrifying historical file entries tracking Project Timelock.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="chapter-card">
                <span class="chapter-num">Chapter 8</span>
                <h3 class="chapter-title">Shatterpoint</h3>
                <p class="chapter-teaser">In an abandoned coastal installation, Aarav fights a glitched, corrupted echo of himself using short micro-burst rewinds.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="chapter-card">
                <span class="chapter-num">Chapter 9</span>
                <h3 class="chapter-title">Timeline Zero</h3>
                <p class="chapter-teaser">A dynamic holograph forces Aarav to choose between systematic cold survival execution or entering a dangerous rewritten dawn.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="quotes" class="container">
        <span class="section-label">Fragments</span>
        <h2 class="section-heading">Stolen Frequency</h2>
        <div class="quotes-container">
            <div class="featured-quote-block">
                <p class="featured-quote-text">"What if it's not death following me? What if it's... me?"</p>
                <span class="featured-quote-author">Aarav — Chapter 2</span>
            </div>
            <div class="quotes-subgrid">
                <div class="quote-card">
                    <p class="quote-card-text">"I became the version of us that lived."</p>
                    <span class="quote-card-context">Future Aarav</span>
                </div>
                <div class="quote-card">
                    <p class="quote-card-text">"Time doesn't heal. It warns."</p>
                    <span class="quote-card-context">Archived Data Streams</span>
                </div>
                <div class="quote-card">
                    <p class="quote-card-text">"The cycle doesn't end because of time. It ends because you trust again."</p>
                    <span class="quote-card-context">The Unbroken Echo</span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="journey" class="container">
        <span class="section-label">Progression</span>
        <h2 class="section-heading">The Loop Path</h2>
        <div class="timeline">
            <div class="timeline-item">
                <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                <div class="timeline-card">
                    <span class="timeline-stage">The Catalyst</span>
                    <h3 class="timeline-title">The Sharma Household Silence</h3>
                    <p class="timeline-desc">A five-minute phone call separates Aarav from a double murder, leaving Meera's parents dead with vacant, unexplainable expressions.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-item">
                <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                <div class="timeline-card">
                    <span class="timeline-stage">Discovery</span>
                    <h3 class="timeline-title">The Three-Second Shadow</h3>
                    <p class="timeline-desc">Aarav extracts a local hard drive, enhancing contrast to find a figure holding his exact physiological stance during an electrical freeze.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-item">
                <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                <div class="timeline-card">
                    <span class="timeline-stage">Confrontation</span>
                    <h3 class="timeline-title">The Warehouse Paradox</h3>
                    <p class="timeline-desc">A trap involving a staged shoot lures Future Aarav out. The older self reveals he spent five loops executing future betrayers beforehand.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-item">
                <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                <div class="timeline-card">
                    <span class="timeline-stage">Awakening</span>
                    <h3 class="timeline-title">Testing the Limits</h3>
                    <p class="timeline-desc">The Chrono Seal manifests on Aarav's hand, allowing brief mechanical rewinds to alter active reality trajectories.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-item">
                <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                <div class="timeline-card">
                    <span class="timeline-stage">Climax</span>
                    <h3 class="timeline-title">The Hourglass Overclock</h3>
                    <p class="timeline-desc">In a coastal facility tracking Subject 43AAR, Aarav smashes a frozen clock device into the core terminal to assert control his own way.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="ending-section">
        <div class="ending-content">
            <span class="section-label">Convergence</span>
            <h2 class="section-heading">A Choice Diverged</h2>
            <p class="ending-message">
                Perfection is an illusion spun by fear. Real life isn't found inside a loop of preemptive strikes, but in the volatile, unpredictable beauty of moving forward.
            </p>
            <p class="ending-quote">"No loops. No shadows. Just time, moving forward."</p>
            <span class="ending-reflection">The Loop is Broken</span>
        </div>
    </section>

    <footer class="footer">
        <div class="footer-title">CHRONO VENDETTA</div>
        <div class="footer-author">Deva Harsha V</div>
        <p class="footer-quote">"Iteration Complete. Awaiting next choice."</p>
    </footer>

    <script>
        document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
            const sections = document.querySelectorAll('section');
            const navLinks = document.querySelectorAll('.nav-links a');

            window.addEventListener('scroll', () => {
                let current = '';
                sections.forEach(section => {
                    const sectionTop = section.offsetTop;
                    const sectionHeight = section.clientHeight;
                    if (pageYOffset >= (sectionTop - 200)) {
                        current = section.getAttribute('id');
                    }
                });

                navLinks.forEach(link => {
                    link.classList.remove('active');
                    if (link.getAttribute('href').slice(1) === current) {
                        link.classList.add('active');
                    }
                });
            });
        });
    </script>
<%- include('partials/footer') %>